    • Constructor Detail

      • Dump

        public Dump(CommunicationResource<P> resource)
        Creates a Dump object over a given resource. This object shows both incoming and outgoing traffic and uses the payload's own toString method as formatting style.
        Parameters:
        resource - the communication resource to be monitored.

      • Dump

        public Dump(CommunicationResource<P> resource,
            Dump.Show show)
        Creates a Dump object over a given resource showing the traffic as specified by the user. This object uses the payload's own toString method as formatting style.
        Parameters:
        resource - the communication resource to be monitored.
        show - a Dump.Show indicating what type of traffic will be shown: whether incoming, outgoing or both.

      • Dump

        public Dump(CommunicationResource<P> resource,
            java.util.function.Function<P,java.lang.String> formatting)
        Creates a Dump object over a given resource using a formatting for the payload specified by the user. This object shows both incoming and outgoing traffic.
        Parameters:
        resource - the communication resource to be monitored.
        formatting - the formatting to be used to display the payload on screen. It must be able to handle the case where the payload is null.

      • Dump

        Parameters:
        resource - the communication resource to be monitored.
        formatting - the formatting to be used to display the payload on screen. It must be able to handle the case where the payload is null.
        show - a Dump.Show indicating what type of traffic will be shown: whether incoming, outgoing or both.
